==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rotunda
<hw>Ro*tun"da</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. It.
<ets>rotonda</ets>, F. <ets>rotonde</ets>; both fr. L.
<ets>rotundus</ets> round. See <er>Rotund</er>, <pos>a.</pos>]</ety>
<fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>A round building; especially, one that is round
both on the outside and inside, like the Pantheon at Rome. Less
properly, but very commonly, used for a large round room; <as>as, the
<ex>rotunda</ex> of the Capitol at Washington</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rotundate</ent>⟦br⟧
